    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "About Cluely\n\nCluely is building AI to give you an unfair advantage in every situation.\n\nIt acts as a desktop assistant that takes in screen, mic, and audio context to give you information and suggestions that existing model providers cannot, due to a lack of context.\n\nWe will win for two reasons:\n\n1) Chatbots are not the best interface for multi-modal AI\n\n2) We can make anything viral\n\nAbout the Role\n\nWe work six days a week in-person in San Francisco, 10-12 hours a day.\n\nYou are expected to live within a block of the office (housing provided).\n\nThe entire codebase is strictly typed (no ts-ignore or anys). We use Bun, Elysia https://elysiajs.com, and strictly typed routes.\n\nYou might be a good fit if you are:\n\n - One of the best engineers in the world\n\n - Strong fullstack engineer (React/Electron/Infra experience)\n   \n   - You should know how to efficiently fetch and cache data in a React application\n   \n   - You should know how to design and structure database schemas that optimize read and write performance\n   \n   - You should be comfortable deploying and scaling applications and be able to weigh pros and cons of different infra/devops solutions\n   \n   - I will sanity check all of the above in an interview with you\n\n - Down to gamble your life into greatness\n\nCompensation:\n\n - Founding engineers get anywhere from $250k-$350k base + 0.25-0.5% equity\n\n - We also offer free food",
